		<scopecontent>
		<p>The Executive Authority to Sell Transports subseries, 1833-1857, contains letters from the Executive Department (the Governor's Office) to the Auditor of Public Accounts.  The letters order the Auditor to receive payment for slaves marked for sale and transportation.  The letters include the purchasers name and the amount owed.  The letters do not include any information about the slaves purchased or where they would be transported.  		</p>
